abstract: The Vermont senator’s criticism of the Center for American Progress threatens to inflame the ideological divisions that roiled the Democratic Party in 2016.
snippet: The Vermont senator’s criticism of the Center for American Progress threatens to inflame the ideological divisions that roiled the Democratic Party in 2016.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Senator Bernie Sanders, in a rare and forceful rebuke by a presidential candidate of an influential party ally, has accused a liberal think tank of undermining Democrats’ chances of taking back the White House in 2020 by “using its resources to smear” him and other contenders pushing progressive policies.

headline_main: 2020 Presidential Candidates’ Tax Returns So Far
byline_original: By Thomas Kaplan, K.K. Rebecca Lai, Jasmine C. Lee and Denise Lu

abstract: Persephone Books in London — devoted mostly to overlooked works by female writers in the mid-1900s — celebrates its 20th anniversary this year.
snippet: Persephone Books in London — devoted mostly to overlooked works by female writers in the mid-1900s — celebrates its 20th anniversary this year.
lead_paragraph: LONDON — Lamb’s Conduit Street seems almost too adorable to be real, as if Ye Olde Fantasy Englande, the one that exists in your head, had suddenly sprung to life. But it feels exactly right that this cobblestone thoroughfare in Bloomsbury, filled as it is with idiosyncratic shops selling artisanal cheese and homemade cakes and other rarefied items, should also be home to Persephone Books, a gem of a place devoted mostly to overlooked works by female writers of the mid-20th century.

headline_print_headline: Shelf Space for the Unsung Female Writer

abstract: In his writings as a student and young politician, he fixated on the kind of media narratives that have propelled his 2020 campaign.
snippet: In his writings as a student and young politician, he fixated on the kind of media narratives that have propelled his 2020 campaign.
lead_paragraph: The question was simple enough, but Senator John Edwards squirmed painfully. For 49 long seconds, the North Carolina Democrat, a masterful courtroom orator, sputtered before a crowd at Harvard, unable to settle on a favorite movie.

abstract: It’s been a busy week in American politics. Here are some of the stories you might have missed.
snippet: It’s been a busy week in American politics. Here are some of the stories you might have missed.
lead_paragraph: From a Department of Homeland Security shake-up to the arrest of Julian Assange, it’s been a busy week in American politics. Here are some of the biggest stories you might have missed (and some links if you’d like to read further).
headline_main: On Politics: The Biggest Stories of the Week

abstract: The attack amplified a controversy that has been a focus of conservative news outlets, which have sought to elevate Ms. Omar, a Muslim lawmaker, as a political target.
snippet: The attack amplified a controversy that has been a focus of conservative news outlets, which have sought to elevate Ms. Omar, a Muslim lawmaker, as a political target.
lead_paragraph: President Trump on Friday targeted Representative Ilhan Omar for remarks she made during a speech on civil rights and Muslims in America with a graphic video featuring the burning World Trade Center towers and other images from Sept. 11, 2001, that he tweeted to millions of his followers.

headline_main: DealBook Briefing: Uber’s Growth Is Slowing

abstract: The debate on when it is relevant to apologize and pay reparations for misdeeds and human rights violations tells us that the past is never dead.
snippet: The debate on when it is relevant to apologize and pay reparations for misdeeds and human rights violations tells us that the past is never dead.
lead_paragraph: MEXICO CITY — Three weeks ago and 500 years after the arrival of Hernán Cortés in Veracruz, President Andrés Manuel López Obrador of Mexico sent a letter to the king of Spain. In it, he demanded an apology for the abuses inflicted on the indigenous peoples of Mexico by Spain, in view of what the Spaniards now consider “human rights violations.”

abstract: Maine and Vermont allow inmates to cast ballots. The 48 other states should too.

lead_paragraph: At a forum in Iowa last weekend, Senator Elizabeth Warren of Massachusetts gave what has become a standard answer for Democrats on the question of felon disenfranchisement.
